eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has more details. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Residents of Westbury in Johannesburg say they fear for their lives. This comes after 13 people were shot over what has turned out to be a bloody weekend. READ: Crime in SA | Westbury residents demand justice Gang violence is believed to be behind the shootings. An 18-year-old was shot on Monday morning. It is understood the killings are retaliatory attacks after the gunning down of Fast guns leader Keenan Ebrahim last Thursday. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has more details in the video above.